headlines.description: — This time, the surging Boston Celtics topped the Detroit Pistons.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Tatum lead Celtics to revenge win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Trae Young knows what the Atlanta Hawks need from him to improve their playoff position, so it was time for a bounce-back game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young regroups with 41 points as Hawks top Raptors, 127-100

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 23 points and All-Star center Jarrett Allen had 18 points and 14 rebounds in rallying the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 92-86 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Markkanen scores 23, Cavaliers rally past Wizards, 92-86

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Gregg Popovich is going to have to wait at least a couple more days before tying the NBA record for regular-season victories.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 36 points, Heat top Popovich, Spurs 133-129

headlines.description: — Ja Morant spun and flipped in an over-the-shoulder layup. He threw down a vicious alley-oop dunk.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores career-high 46, Grizzlies beat Bulls 116-110

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving enjoyed this trip to Fiserv Forum much better than his last visit.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving has season-high 38, Nets rally to beat Bucks 126-123

headlines.description: — Monte Morris hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 28 seconds left, Nikola Jokic had 18 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Sacramento Kings 115-110 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic's triple-double leads Nuggets over Kings, 115-110
